Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:

44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.37e78184-2794-4dd5-8f22-529a4b7b3745.prompt=host to test connection from 44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.3912fe43-bbde-4584-af8a-7e092c229622.transition.description=${keyName} cleared for storing ping summary. 44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.3c5f1a06-d9be-4314-95cb-f4f7263dfd88.prompt=Enter a comma delimited list of hosts to test connection to 44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.3e6430fc-73e3-404f-b9c4-8a5f3c6c9dbf.description=
Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way.

Inputs\:
notifyData -  The text of the notification message.
notifyMethod - The method of notification (Write to File, Email, Display or None).
subject - A description of what the notification is about.
destination - The destination of the notification (email address or filename). This field is required when notifyMethod is Email or Write to File.
notificationServer - The email server to send the notification through. This field is required when notifyMethod is Email.
from -The originator of the message (email "from" address).This field is required when notifyMethod is Email.
serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. This field used when notifyMethod is Email, and it is optional (it defaults to 25 if not specified).

Responses\:
success - The user was notified.
failure - Notification failed.

As mentioned above, some inputs are required for certain types of notification methods. In order to schedule a flow that in turn uses this flow, all of the required fields for the given notification method must be supplied, or else the flow will not be able to execute to completion. For example, if "notifyMethod" is "File", then the "destination" input must also be specified.
44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.40a24ecf-b992-4b49-9284-5ed74e312336.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.description=
Tests the connections to a given list of hosts.

Inputs\:
host - A host to ping from.
username - a username for the host.
password - password for hosts.
targets - list of hosts to ping.
lossThreshold - The maximum % packet loss that is considered acceptable.
latencyThreshold - The maximum number of milliseconds of latency that are acceptable.
delimiter - A delimiter that separates the different targets.
notifyMethod - How to give the report to the user.

Returns\:
A message listing hosts that have failed their connection tests.

Responses\:
success - All targets passed test.
diagnosed - One or more targets failed the test.
failure - something went wrong.

44fd8a10-0eec-4505-8cfe-b006828ffc2c.f8b98b30-4336-40a3-a4ca-0e7dc4411751.description=
Checks to see whether or not a connection exists, and if it exists checks to see if it is adequately reliable.

Inputs\:
host - The host to ping from.
username - The username for host.
password - The password for host.
lossThreshold - What percentage of packet loss you consider to be acceptable for this connection.
latencyThreshold - How long (in milliseconds) you consider to be an acceptable latency for this connection.
target - The host to ping.
characterSet - The character encoding of the target computer. The default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - The test passed.
diagnosed - A problem was found.
failure - Something went wrong.

Notes\:
1.The character encoding specified in the input for characterSet must be compatible for the host and RAS systems, otherwise the command file created to execute the command becomes garbled causing an error while executing.
2. Recommended Thresholds\:
Connection Type		Loss Threshold (%)	Latency Threshold (ms)
DSL modem			2		200
Cable modem		2		200
dialup modem		2		500
ISDN Line			2		150
T1/T3/OCR			2		80
10 ethernet			2		10
Wireless			2		600
